For added security, thereâ€™s a new step to authenticate to an external system for external credentials that use OAuth 2.0 authentication with the Browser Flow. Now, after you authenticate, you must confirm that you want your Salesforce org to interact with the external system on your behalf. Previously, the final step was to authenticate into the external system.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in all editions.

How: From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Named Credentials, and then select Named Credentials. Create or edit an external credential that uses the OAuth 2.0 authentication protocol with the Browser Flow, create a principal, and authenticate into the external system. Return to Salesforce and confirm that you want to allow Salesforce to access the external system.

Create or Edit an OAuth External Credential with the Browser Flow
title: Confirming Access to External Systems in Salesforce
